Heat the oil and butter in a large heavy-based casserole. Add the onions and fry for several minutes on a medium heat until starting to caramelise. Add all the remaining ingredients, then season with salt and pepper.Bring to the boil, then turn down and cover. Leave to simmer for around 30 minutes, stirring fairly regularly, then remove the lid and turn up the heat slightly.Continue to cook until the liquid has reduced and is starting to become syrupy. Check the seasoning and serve.